If anger comes, you identify it. And you try to think of peace, love, compassion, etc. If you deny that you&#8217;re angry, then you can&#8217;t replace the anger. <span class=date>10/21/79</span>
<br>Q: In sananda samadhi, bliss is experienced in the whole body.
<br>A: The only object of concentration in sananda is bliss that one is feeling as a result of knowledge gained in the previous samadhis. <span class=date>10/21/79</span>
